58:48.363 --> 58:50.600
<i>They always tell you that
if you have a problem,</i>

58:50.601 --> 58:52.603
<i>Talk to your
Congressman.</i>

58:52.604 --> 58:55.642
<i>Lucky for me, my
Congressman is Henry Waxman.</i>

58:55.643 --> 58:57.445
- Hey, how are you?
- I'm fine. How are you?

58:57.446 --> 58:58.982
Very nice to meet you.
Chris Bell.

58:58.983 --> 59:00.351
<i>He's the one who called</i>

59:00.352 --> 59:02.354
<i>the baseball hearings
in the first place.</i>

59:02.355 --> 59:04.358
<i>He's got to have
some answers.</i>

59:04.359 --> 59:06.362
I think it's important

59:06.363 --> 59:09.133
for sports figures

59:09.134 --> 59:11.571
in major league sports

59:11.572 --> 59:13.575
not to be allowed

59:13.576 --> 59:16.647
to use steroids
under any circumstance.

59:16.648 --> 59:18.517
And for young people--

59:18.518 --> 59:21.155
we certainly don't want
them to be using it.

59:21.156 --> 59:24.428
So the drug is
a restricted drug.

59:24.429 --> 59:27.033
It's not--
there's not a--

59:27.034 --> 59:29.738
Let me--

59:29.739 --> 59:32.075
Brian, is it illegal
to use--?

59:32.076 --> 59:33.946
it's illegal--
it's legal

59:33.947 --> 59:35.615
under some circumstances.
What's--?

59:35.616 --> 59:37.352
<i>It's legal
with a prescription--</i>

59:37.353 --> 59:39.623
<i>- legal with-- okay.
- --A medical prescription.</i>

59:39.624 --> 59:41.493
It's legal with
a medical prescription.

59:41.494 --> 59:43.397
And the other drug
was the...

59:43.398 --> 59:45.567
testosterone or just
steroids in general.

59:45.568 --> 59:47.938
Well, I think that
they're also banned.

59:47.939 --> 59:50.543
They're already banned
in professional sports.

59:50.544 --> 59:52.814
Brian, am I right?
Speak up if I'm wrong.

59:52.815 --> 59:53.983
<i>- Yes.
- Okay.</i>

59:53.984 --> 59:56.254
Well, these products
are already banned.

59:56.255 --> 59:59.359
Cigarettes
and alcohol

59:59.360 --> 01:00:01.363
are legally
available,

01:00:01.364 --> 01:00:04.168
but not if you're
under the age.

01:00:04.169 --> 01:00:06.172
And I think the age

01:00:06.173 --> 01:00:08.943
is 18 for both
all around the country.

01:00:08.944 --> 01:00:12.116
Is it 18 or 21? I'm
getting confused. What?

01:00:12.117 --> 01:00:13.618
<i>21.
21.</i>

01:00:13.619 --> 01:00:15.556
- Okay, so strike that.
- That's all right.

01:00:15.557 --> 01:00:17.593
<i>President Bush allotted</i>

01:00:17.594 --> 01:00:20.031
<i>$15 million
for steroid education.</i>

01:00:20.032 --> 01:00:21.967
<i>Where has
that money gone?</i>

01:00:21.968 --> 01:00:24.706
Um, I don't know.

01:00:24.707 --> 01:00:27.177
Do you know?

01:00:27.178 --> 01:00:28.680
Okay, we don't know.

01:00:28.681 --> 01:00:31.518
<i>- Okay.
- So...</i>

01:00:31.519 --> 01:00:33.522
It's a war on drugs

01:00:33.523 --> 01:00:35.559
and Congressmen want
to be tough on drugs,

01:00:35.560 --> 01:00:37.562
so they just
demonize them all.

01:00:37.563 --> 01:00:39.700
And they say, "oh, our children
are being exposed to them.

01:00:39.701 --> 01:00:41.704
They're gonna kill
our children."

01:00:41.705 --> 01:00:44.142
And they just paint
everything in black and white.

01:00:44.143 --> 01:00:46.413
And they really don't
see the areas in between.

01:00:46.414 --> 01:00:48.617
For those of us
who live in the grey areas

01:00:48.618 --> 01:00:50.453
and whose life
depends on it.

01:00:50.454 --> 01:00:52.055
It's a very
important issue.

01:00:52.056 --> 01:00:54.260
Politicians
are always looking

01:00:54.261 --> 01:00:56.297
for an issue
to get behind.

01:00:56.298 --> 01:00:58.134
They're always looking
for something

01:00:58.135 --> 01:00:59.970
to be able to say
to the public,

01:00:59.971 --> 01:01:01.841
"hey, look at what
my legislation's doing.

01:01:01.842 --> 01:01:03.210
Look at what
my bill has done.

01:01:03.211 --> 01:01:06.081
I'm out there.
I'm protecting you.

01:01:06.082 --> 01:01:08.152
I'm protecting
the children."

01:01:08.153 --> 01:01:10.256
<i>Turns out the
most important witness</i>

01:01:10.257 --> 01:01:13.095
<i>at the baseball hearings
was not a famous athlete.</i>

01:01:13.096 --> 01:01:15.566
<i>Taylor Hooton was
a 17-year-old kid</i>

01:01:15.567 --> 01:01:19.005
<i>who committed suicide and
his father blamed steroids.</i>

01:01:19.006 --> 01:01:21.911
I believe
the poor example

01:01:21.912 --> 01:01:24.249
being set
by professional athletes

01:01:24.250 --> 01:01:26.720
is a major catalyst
fueling

01:01:26.721 --> 01:01:29.091
the high usage of steroids
amongst our kids.

01:01:29.092 --> 01:01:31.328
And parents
across America

01:01:31.329 --> 01:01:33.665
should hold you
accountable

01:01:33.666 --> 01:01:36.070
for behavior
that inspires our kids

01:01:36.071 --> 01:01:38.474
to do things that put
their health at risk

01:01:38.475 --> 01:01:40.478
and that teaches them
that the ethics

01:01:40.479 --> 01:01:42.983
we try to teach them
around our kitchen table

01:01:42.984 --> 01:01:45.454
somehow don't apply
to them.

01:01:45.455 --> 01:01:47.458
Please help us to see

01:01:47.459 --> 01:01:50.129
that our children's lives
were not lost in vain.

01:01:50.130 --> 01:01:52.868
You have the power
to do something about it

01:01:52.869 --> 01:01:55.706
and we're counting
on you to do so.

01:01:55.707 --> 01:01:57.442
<i>Donald Hooton coming in</i>

01:01:57.443 --> 01:01:59.180
<i>and putting
a human face on it</i>

01:01:59.181 --> 01:02:02.653
was more powerful
than the scientific--

01:02:02.654 --> 01:02:04.957
the statistics
or any of that stuff.

01:02:04.958 --> 01:02:07.628
<i>On average,
5,000 kids a year</i>

01:02:07.629 --> 01:02:09.666
<i>commit suicide
in America.</i>

01:02:09.667 --> 01:02:12.337
<i>And most parents
never know exactly why.</i>

01:02:12.338 --> 01:02:14.675
<i>I wanted to find out why
Donald Hooton is so sure</i>

01:02:14.676 --> 01:02:17.279
<i>that the answer could
be as simple as steroids.</i>

01:02:25.229 --> 01:02:26.730
- How are you doing?
- Fine.

01:02:26.731 --> 01:02:28.834
- Chris Henry.
- Don Hooton. Nice to meet you.

01:02:28.835 --> 01:02:32.139
This is a very very
competitive community

01:02:32.140 --> 01:02:34.612
all the way from
athletics to business.

01:02:34.613 --> 01:02:37.850
So you wind up
in an affluent area

01:02:37.851 --> 01:02:41.156
where these kids can afford
to play with this stuff.

01:02:41.157 --> 01:02:43.494
<i>And of course in
hindsight as we look back,</i>

01:02:43.495 --> 01:02:45.598
<i>all of the signs were
staring us in the face--</i>

01:02:45.599 --> 01:02:48.170
The behavior problems,
the physical changes,

01:02:48.171 --> 01:02:50.440
but we had no idea
what we were looking at.

01:02:50.441 --> 01:02:52.410
If we go back
to the medical textbook,

01:02:52.411 --> 01:02:55.316
the depression that comes
along with steroid use is bad,

01:02:55.317 --> 01:02:58.656
<i>but it's worse in that
four-to-six-week period</i>

01:02:58.657 --> 01:03:01.160
<i>following stopping
using this stuff.</i>

01:03:01.161 --> 01:03:03.431
<i>And it was
during that period</i>

01:03:03.432 --> 01:03:05.434
that his mother
found him

01:03:05.435 --> 01:03:07.939
hanging on the door
in his bedroom.

01:03:07.940 --> 01:03:09.275
<i>Jeez.</i>

01:03:09.276 --> 01:03:11.278
Taylor Hooton's dad,
Don Hooton,

01:03:11.279 --> 01:03:14.484
called me shortly after

01:03:14.485 --> 01:03:17.056
Taylor had taken
his life.

01:03:17.057 --> 01:03:19.760
Together we came up
with the idea

01:03:19.761 --> 01:03:21.865
of creating
a private organization...

01:03:21.866 --> 01:03:23.835
...to educate
the public

01:03:23.836 --> 01:03:25.838
<i>about the dangers</i>

01:03:25.839 --> 01:03:28.142
<i>of anabolic steroid abuse.</i>

01:03:28.143 --> 01:03:30.013
This is Taylor's room.

01:03:30.014 --> 01:03:31.850
You don't have to come
in here long to realize

01:03:31.851 --> 01:03:33.519
Taylor was
a baseball player.

01:03:33.520 --> 01:03:37.560
<i>'Cause he started maybe
five years old in T-ball.</i>

01:03:37.561 --> 01:03:41.601
<i>But Taylor was
a great kid.</i>

01:03:41.602 --> 01:03:43.872
We took Taylor
to a psychiatrist

01:03:43.873 --> 01:03:46.810
<i>and she put him on
a low dose of Lexapro.</i>

01:03:46.811 --> 01:03:49.282
<i>And as far as I know,</i>

01:03:49.283 --> 01:03:51.920
this is the only
steroid-related case

01:03:51.921 --> 01:03:55.694
that this well-meaning
psychiatrist had ever had.

01:03:55.695 --> 01:03:59.367
And when the psychiatrist
recommended that Taylor go cold turkey

01:03:59.368 --> 01:04:01.705
and stop using steroids...

01:04:03.742 --> 01:04:05.912
it was a formula
for disaster.

01:04:05.913 --> 01:04:08.250
I feel terrible, obviously,
about Taylor Hooton,

01:04:08.251 --> 01:04:10.621
But Taylor Hooton had
a lot of problems

01:04:10.622 --> 01:04:12.625
and he was on other drugs.

01:04:12.626 --> 01:04:14.628
According to some
newspaper accounts,

01:04:14.629 --> 01:04:17.233
he was on S.S.R.I.S--
antidepressants

01:04:17.234 --> 01:04:19.236
which have been shown
to be associated

01:04:19.237 --> 01:04:22.142
with suicidal ideation
and suicidal behavior.

01:04:22.143 --> 01:04:25.047
<i>So whether his suicide
was due to Lexapro</i>

01:04:25.048 --> 01:04:27.185
<i>or due to steroids
or due to depression</i>

01:04:27.186 --> 01:04:29.522
<i>or due to stress
of being a great athlete,</i>

01:04:29.523 --> 01:04:31.693
<i>there are five other
things-- I don't know.</i>

01:04:31.694 --> 01:04:33.831
Do you think
that perhaps--

01:04:33.832 --> 01:04:36.636
when I look
at your website,

01:04:36.637 --> 01:04:39.440
The Taylor Hooton
Foundation--

01:04:39.441 --> 01:04:41.845
do you think
it's a responsibility

01:04:41.846 --> 01:04:45.652
to include
antidepressants in there

01:04:45.653 --> 01:04:47.656
just in case
there are critics

01:04:47.657 --> 01:04:49.660
or just to raise
the awareness

01:04:49.661 --> 01:04:52.398
of how dangerous perhaps
antidepressants may be?

01:04:52.399 --> 01:04:54.402
No, I don't.
And the reason is,

01:04:54.403 --> 01:04:57.540
our battle is not with antidepressants.
Our battle's with steroids.

01:04:57.541 --> 01:05:00.479
<i>The National Institute
on Drug Abuse said</i>

01:05:00.480 --> 01:05:02.483
the dangers
of anabolic steroids

01:05:02.484 --> 01:05:04.955
are temporary
and reversible.

01:05:04.956 --> 01:05:06.958
My son is dead.

01:05:09.263 --> 01:05:12.802
All of the intellectual
arguments

01:05:12.803 --> 01:05:14.271
about whether or not

01:05:14.272 --> 01:05:17.844
steroids are dangerous
or not

01:05:17.845 --> 01:05:19.848
don't matter to me.

01:05:19.849 --> 01:05:21.785
I know
they're dangerous.

01:05:21.786 --> 01:05:25.092
<i>I saw it with my own eyes
and I watched my son die.</i>

01:05:25.093 --> 01:05:27.763
The only evidence I need
is the pictures of my son

01:05:27.764 --> 01:05:29.766
that are on the wall
behind you.

01:05:29.767 --> 01:05:30.668
Mm-hmm.

01:05:33.541 --> 01:05:35.510
Look, I have a son too.

01:05:35.511 --> 01:05:38.182
And the last thing in the
world I could ever imagine doing

01:05:38.183 --> 01:05:40.119
is burying that kid.
And it would probably

01:05:40.120 --> 01:05:41.889
ruin me for the rest
of my life.

01:05:41.890 --> 01:05:44.059
And I can see
where having a cause

01:05:44.060 --> 01:05:46.798
to sort of assuage
the feelings of guilt

01:05:46.799 --> 01:05:49.870
and depression that are
following my son's death

01:05:49.871 --> 01:05:53.043
would probably be helpful. "Let's
not let this happen to somebody else."

01:05:53.044 --> 01:05:55.514
But they're chasing
the wrong thing.

01:05:55.515 --> 01:05:57.083
They're not
doing it right.

01:05:57.084 --> 01:05:59.087
We're working
with major league baseball

01:05:59.088 --> 01:06:01.091
to make that happen now

01:06:01.092 --> 01:06:03.662
where hopefully
in each local stadium

01:06:03.663 --> 01:06:06.100
<i>there's gonna be
a steroid awareness night.</i>

01:06:06.101 --> 01:06:08.104
Do you find it
ironic at all

01:06:08.105 --> 01:06:11.142
to have a steroid
awareness night for baseball

01:06:11.143 --> 01:06:13.113
in a stadium
that sells alcohol

01:06:13.114 --> 01:06:15.484
which is responsible for
a lot of deaths as a drug?

01:06:17.789 --> 01:06:19.624
Alcohol's legal to sell.

01:06:19.625 --> 01:06:21.628
<i>And we can argue
all day long</i>

01:06:21.629 --> 01:06:25.702
<i>Whether tobacco kills
and whether alcohol kills,</i>

01:06:25.703 --> 01:06:27.706
and there's a clear
distinction in my mind

01:06:27.707 --> 01:06:30.478
between tobacco
or alcohol

01:06:30.479 --> 01:06:33.884
and steroids and
methamphetamines and coke.

01:06:33.885 --> 01:06:35.654
- Thanks for sharing that with us.
- All right.

01:06:35.655 --> 01:06:37.557
I know how hard
it can be and everything.

01:06:37.558 --> 01:06:38.659
This is
important stuff.

01:06:54.122 --> 01:06:56.492
<i>Anybody who
asks me about it--</i>

01:06:56.493 --> 01:06:58.329
<i>I let them know.
I tell them why.</i>

01:06:58.330 --> 01:07:01.234
<i>I tell them how much I
take. I'll tell them anything</i>

01:07:01.235 --> 01:07:04.240
<i>- they want to ask me about them
'cause I think-- - What about the kids?</i>

01:07:04.241 --> 01:07:07.079
The kids are different
because--

01:07:07.080 --> 01:07:09.716
<i>a couple kids asked me in
front of the whole group</i>

01:07:09.717 --> 01:07:11.320
<i>and I had to lie
about it</i>

01:07:11.321 --> 01:07:13.825
because this whole steroid
thing is just out of hand.

01:07:13.826 --> 01:07:15.929
I know coach Henry
doesn't take any steroids.

01:07:15.930 --> 01:07:18.032
He's just 100% strong.

01:07:18.033 --> 01:07:20.570
<i>I think somebody asked
him if he was on steroids</i>

01:07:20.571 --> 01:07:23.309
and he said no. And I
completely believe him.

01:07:23.310 --> 01:07:25.412
He just teaches that
steroids are basically--

01:07:25.413 --> 01:07:27.249
they're a cheap way
out of doing hard work.

01:07:27.250 --> 01:07:29.620
<i>I say they're not for kids.</i>

01:07:29.621 --> 01:07:32.592
<i>Steroids are not for kids.
That's plain and simple.</i>

01:07:32.593 --> 01:07:34.696
<i>You should achieve
things naturally</i>

01:07:34.697 --> 01:07:36.666
<i>and then maybe you
should think about them</i>

01:07:36.667 --> 01:07:38.269
<i>when you're
an adult.</i>

01:07:38.270 --> 01:07:40.273
The main reason why
I don't take steroids

01:07:40.274 --> 01:07:42.778
is 'cause he got it into my
head that I don't need 'em,

01:07:42.779 --> 01:07:46.184
that I got the potential right now as
a teenager to get as strong as I want.

01:07:46.185 --> 01:07:48.822
<i>What good would it do them
to know that I take steroids?</i>

01:07:48.823 --> 01:07:51.226
<i>It wouldn't do them any
good. They'd just be like,</i>

01:07:51.227 --> 01:07:53.597
<i>"oh, man,
he's a cheater.</i>

01:07:53.598 --> 01:07:55.468
<i>Would you ever tell our
parents that you do it?</i>

01:07:55.469 --> 01:07:59.041
Um, I mean, you know,

01:07:59.042 --> 01:08:01.044
if they asked me.

01:08:01.045 --> 01:08:03.983
I only cooked
two pounds.

01:08:03.984 --> 01:08:06.688
I hope it's enough.

01:08:06.689 --> 01:08:09.026
<i>You know, we went
to church all the time.</i>

01:08:09.027 --> 01:08:10.930
I grew up
in a great family.

01:08:10.931 --> 01:08:12.933
I don't think
I could ask

01:08:12.934 --> 01:08:15.337
for anybody better
to be parents, you know.

01:08:15.338 --> 01:08:19.879
And when I went
to the U.S.C.

01:08:19.880 --> 01:08:21.950
<i>I didn't do any drugs.
I didn't do anything.</i>

01:08:21.951 --> 01:08:24.254
<i>- 'Cause you're a good boy.
- Well...</i>

01:08:24.255 --> 01:08:26.792
And then I got to a point
where I actually tried steroids.

01:08:26.792 --> 01:08:29.430
<i>I tried Winstrol,
which is injections.</i>

01:08:29.430 --> 01:08:31.667
You injected a needle
in yourself?

01:08:31.667 --> 01:08:33.237
<i>It's just
in the muscle.</i>

01:08:33.238 --> 01:08:34.939
Yeah, 'cause you get to
a point where you're like,

01:08:34.941 --> 01:08:37.145
"I'm getting out of shape.
I don't feel like I used to."

01:08:37.145 --> 01:08:39.148
<i>The reason I stopped
doing it was</i>

01:08:39.149 --> 01:08:41.519
<i>because I thought
it was immoral.</i>

01:08:41.520 --> 01:08:43.990
<i>I thought it was so wrong
and like,</i>

01:08:43.991 --> 01:08:46.194
"what if my parents
found out I did this?"

01:08:46.194 --> 01:08:48.031
I think it's really
hard to hear

01:08:48.032 --> 01:08:51.170
- that you tried 'em and everything, but--
- For you.

01:08:51.171 --> 01:08:52.640
It's not hard
for me.

01:08:52.640 --> 01:08:55.877
What I'm saying is
that it's hard to hear.

01:08:55.879 --> 01:08:57.881
And what about mark?
I mean,

01:08:57.883 --> 01:09:00.453
how come you're staying big
but you're not getting fat?

01:09:00.453 --> 01:09:02.925
- You're just--
- I'm getting fatter.

01:09:02.926 --> 01:09:04.862
No, but your face
is rounder.

01:09:04.863 --> 01:09:07.033
- I put on body fat.
He's about--

01:09:07.033 --> 01:09:09.804
<i>You're about 7% or 8% higher than what
you normally are, wouldn't you say?</i>

01:09:09.805 --> 01:09:11.506
I have no idea. I don't
really care either.

01:09:11.508 --> 01:09:13.176
<i>He's already
married. He doesn't care.</i>

01:09:13.178 --> 01:09:15.448
Except Smelly's
not saying anything.

01:09:15.448 --> 01:09:18.086
Don't let your brothers
overrun your conversation.

01:09:20.390 --> 01:09:22.661
When you get
caught with something

01:09:22.662 --> 01:09:26.001
I think the truth is
always the fastest way

